  <section id="insurance-options">
    <h2>Insurance Options for Retirees</h2>
    <p>
      New Zealand's healthcare is excellent, but non-residents must rely on private coverage. Understanding insurance options helps navigate both visa requirements and practical healthcare access.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>International health insurance</strong> provides comprehensive coverage in New Zealand plus travel and evacuation benefits. For retirees without permanent residence, international coverage ensures healthcare access regardless of visa status changes. Required for most visa applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>New Zealand private insurance</strong> from providers like Southern Cross, NIB, and Partners Life offers local coverage. These plans provide access to private hospitals, specialists, and faster treatment than public waiting lists. Available to residents; some plans accept non-residents.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>ACC (Accident Compensation Corporation):</strong> New Zealand's accident insurance scheme covers everyone in New Zealand for accidents—regardless of visa status. This provides significant protection for accident-related injuries but doesn't cover illness.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Public healthcare access:</strong> Permanent residents and citizens access subsidized public healthcare. Non-residents pay full costs without subsidies—potentially expensive for hospital care. Private insurance is essential for non-residents.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Combination strategies:</strong> Residents often use public healthcare for major needs (covered), private insurance for faster elective access, and international insurance for travel. Non-residents rely on international or NZ private coverage for all care.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="recommended-providers">
    <h2>Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
    <p>
      These international insurers provide comprehensive coverage for New Zealand retirees meeting visa requirements and providing excellent healthcare access.
    </p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />
    <p>
      <strong>Cigna Global</strong> offers strong coverage in New Zealand with established local relationships. Their moratorium underwriting helps those with pre-existing conditions. They accept new members up to 74 and provide seamless international coverage.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Bupa Global</strong> has strong New Zealand and Australia presence with no maximum entry age for existing members. Good choice for those wanting comprehensive Australasian coverage with global benefits.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Aetna International</strong> provides unlimited evacuation and comprehensive global coverage. Their Asia-Pacific operations support New Zealand retirees with regional and worldwide access.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers comprehensive international plans with strong service in the Pacific region. Good choice for those wanting established European insurer with global reach.
    </p>
  </section>

